                <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="content" -->
                <tr bordercolor="#666666">
                  <td colspan="2" valign="top" background="images/hkix_bg_policies.jpg" style="background-repeat:no-repeat" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="normaltext"><P><P>
                    <table width="97%"  border="0" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                      <tr>
                        <td><TABLE cellSpacing=0 width=100% border=0>
                          <TBODY>
                            <TR>
                              <TD height="51"><span class="subhead2">Basic Set-up </span></TD>
                            </TR>
                            <TR>
                              <TD><ul>
                                  <li>In general, HKIX can provide at most two IPv4 and two IPv6 addresses to each participant per HKIX site. </li>
                                  </ul></TD>
                            </TR>
                            
                            <TR>
                              <TD><ul>
                                  <li>HKIX supports at most one IPv4 and one IPv6  address per connection to each participant on HKIX switch per HKIX site.</li>
                                  </ul></TD>
                            </TR>
                            <TR>
                              <TD><ul>
                                  <li>HKIX can provide at most two 10/100/1000BaseT network connections to each participant on HKIX switch per HKIX site.</li>
                                  </ul></TD>
                            </TR>
                            <TR>
                              <TD><ul>
                                  <li>HKIX does not support trunk or VLAN mapping to our switch at both HKIX sites.</li>
                              </ul></TD>
                            </TR>
                            
							
							<TR>
                              <TD><ul>
                                  <li>Participants must DISABLE proxy arp on their router interfaces towards HKIX at all times.</li>
                                  </ul></TD>
                            </TR>
							
							<TR>
                              <TD><ul>
                                  <li>HKIX will turn on port security  with   the  MAC address  connected from  participant's router to the HKIX switch. At any time, only one MAC address will be allowed on each HKIX  port and HKIX participant must inform HKIX NOC by email if there is any change or maintenance on the router MAC address. </li>
                              </ul></TD>
							  </TR>
                            
                            <TR>
                              <TD><ul>
                                  <li>All switching or transmission equipment must be owned and operated by Fixed Telecommunication Network Services Operators and installed in their equipment racks.</li>
                                  </ul></TD>
                            </TR>
                            <TR>
                              <TD height="77"><ul>
                                  <li>The basic set-up is free of charge and no formal agreement is needed to be signed between HKIX and the HKIX participant as long as the participant has fulfilled all the requirements for becoming a HKIX participant as stated in <a href="http://www.hkix.net/hkix/policies.htm" target="_self">http://www.hkix.net/hkix/policies.htm</a>.</li>
                                  </ul></TD>
                            </TR>
                            <TR>
                              <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
                            </TR>
                            <TR>
                              <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
                            </TR>
                          <UL>
                          </UL>
                        </TABLE></td>
                      </tr>
                    </table>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
